CHOLERA - PERU (02)
*******************
A ProMED-mail post
See Also
Cholera - Peru 980212200932
Date: Fri, 13 Feb 1998 10:06:26 +0000
From: Steve Berger <mberger@post.tau.ac.il>

The following background data on cholera in Peru were abstracted from the
GIDEON software program:
During the 1990's, cholera was reported from Amazonas, Ancash, Apurimac,
Arequipa, Ayacucho, Cajamarca, Callao, Cuzco, Huancavelica, Huanuco, Ica,
Junin, La Libertad, Lambayeque, Lima, Loreto, Madre de Dios, Moquegua,
Pasco, Piura, Puno, San Martin,
Tacna, Tumbes and Ucayali departments.
Year Number Fatal
1991 322,562 2,902
1992 212,642 727
1993 71,448 575
1994 23,887 199
1995 22,397 171
1996 4,518 21
1997 * 1,308 0
* Preliminary data
--
Dr. Steve Berger
e-mail: mberger@post.tau.ac.il
[With approximately 3,000 cases reported for January, 1998 (see ProMED-mail
reference cited above) it appears that Peru's steady progress toward
control of cholera has suffered a temporary set-back due to the
ENSO-related increase in rainfall. - Mod.ES
